      },
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "SpecificResource",
          "purpose": "linking",
          "source": "https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/ODE/PicardLindelof.html#IsPicardLindelof.exists_eq_forall_mem_Icc_hasDerivWithinAt",
          "identifier": "IsPicardLindelof.exists_eq_forall_mem_Icc_hasDerivWithinAt"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "classifying",
          "value": "formalized"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "classifying",
          "value": "match_kind:exact"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "tagging",
          "value": "proposition"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Mathlib's Picard–Lindelöf is proved exactly via Banach's theorem applied to the integral (Picard) operator; see `ODE.picard` and `FunSpace.exists_isFixedPt_next` which use `ContractingWith.isFixedPt_fixedPoint_iterate`.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banach_fixed-point_theorem?oldid=1350866762",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "Picard–Lindelöf theorem"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "urn:wikilean:Banach_fixed-point_theorem:anno-7",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": "linking",
      "created": "2026-05-27T20:01:57+00:00",
      "generator": {
        "type": "Software",
        "name": "WikiLean 2-agent annotation pipeline",
        "homepage": "https://github.com/Deicyde/WikiLean"
      },
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "SpecificResource",
          "purpose": "linking",
          "source": "https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/InverseFunctionTheorem/ApproximatesLinearOn.html#ApproximatesLinearOn.toOpenPartialHomeomorph",
          "identifier": "ApproximatesLinearOn.toOpenPartialHomeomorph"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "classifying",
          "value": "partial"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "classifying",
          "value": "match_kind:generalization"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "tagging",
          "value": "proposition"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Mathlib's `ApproximatesLinearOn.toOpenPartialHomeomorph` produces a homeomorphism on a neighborhood (taking `I + g` to its image), but does NOT explicitly carry the bi-Lipschitz conclusion. The article's stronger claim — that `(I+g)^{-1}` is also of the form `I+h` with `h` Lipschitz of constant `k/(1-k)` — does not appear to be a standalone Mathlib decl.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banach_fixed-point_theorem?oldid=1350866762",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "small Lipschitz perturbations of the identity are bi-lipschitz homeomorphisms"
        }
      }
    },
